<img src="https://biz-file.com/c/1903/485543-625x325.jpg?2" alt="WhatsApp to get its own Facebook-made cryptocurrency, report suggests" width="625" height="325">© 123RF.com.Citing five individuals familiar with the matter, the report explains that Facebook’s “working on a coin” that will allow users to send and receive virtual cash to contacts, in a similar vein to Venmo and PayPal.Cryptocurrency publication Coindesk confirmed the validity of the report, speaking to a source of its own.Alongside Facebook’s WhatsApp, two other messaging services Signal and Telegram are also reportedly working on their own digital currencies.